rror%20attack%20on%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20argument%20has%20some%20merit%20given%20its%20oft-repeated%20%E2%80%98no-tolerance%E2%80%99%20policy%20towards%20terrorism%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20ambivalence%20towards%20Hamas%20suggests%20its%20position%20is%20more%20nuanced%20than%20the%20domestic%20debate%20admits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fcurrent-affairs%2Findia-among-32-countries-who-refrained-from-voting-on-anti-hamas-resolution-118120700237_1.html%5C%22%3Eabstained%20in%202018%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20voted%20on%20a%20resolution%20condemning%20Hamas%20for%20%E2%80%9Crepeatedly%20firing%20rockets%20into%20Israel%20and%20for%20inciting%20violence%2C%20thereby%20putting%20civilians%20at%20risk%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%2C%20one%20must%20question%20if%20India%E2%80%99s%20latest%20abstention%20was%20really%20about%20the%20terror%20attacks%20of%20October%207%20not%20being%20mentioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20India%20has%20labelled%20attacks%20by%20Hamas%20as%20%E2%80%98terror%E2%80%99.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20India%20at%20different%20forums%20has%20only%20condemned%20some%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20actions%2C%20whereas%20other%20countries%20explicitly%20called%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20actions%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20May%202021%2C%20when%20Hamas%20launched%20rocket%20and%20mortar%20attacks%20against%20Israel%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-opposes-hamas-rocket-action-against-israel-supports-palestine-101621224892489.html%5C%22%3Eonly%20opposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20firing%20and%20no%20mention%20of%20terror%20attacks%20featured%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpminewyork.gov.in%2FIndiaatUNSC%3Fid%3DNDI0OA%2C%2C%5C%22%3Eits%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2