or%20destroyed%20inventory%20and%20employee%20theft%2C%20to%20name%20a%20couple%20of%20other%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20companies%20such%20as%20Target%20and%20Walgreens%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehave%20cumulatively%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretailers-lost-112-billion-to-inventory-shrink-in-2022%23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20losses%20from%20theft%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20citing%20shrink%20numbers.%20Often%2C%20company%20executives%20use%20%26quot%3Bshrink%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btheft%26quot%3B%20interchangeably%2C%20while%20providing%20no%20breakdown%20of%20how%20much%20of%20their%20shrink%20is%20attributable%20to%20theft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%2C%20for%20example%2C%20previously%20told%20Insider%20that%20missing%20inventory%20at%20its%20stores%20had%20doubled%20since%202019.%20But%20the%20big-box%20chain%20hasn't%20broken%20down%20the%20exact%20causes%20of%20that%20increase.%20Still%2C%20the%20company%20mentioned%20shrink%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20company's%20decision%20in%20September%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-closing-stores-due-to-crime-stats-tell-another-story-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eclose%20nine%20Target%20stores%20across%20the%20US%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Rite%20Aid%20closed%20stores%2C%20its%20chief%20financial%20officer%2C%20Matthew%20Schroeder%2C%20said%20it%20targeted%20%26quot%3Bstores%20in%20high-shrink%20areas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20a%20Home%20Depot%20executive%20responded%20to%20an%20analyst's%20question%20about%20shrink%20on%20an%20earnings%20call%20by%20referencing%20%26quot%3Borganized%20retail%20crime%26quot%3B%20and%20calling%20for%20congressional%20action%20on%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20curb%20the%20sale%20of%20stolen%20goods%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20shrink%20like%20that%20overstates%20the%20impact%20of%20theft%20on%20retailers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20hides%20other%20problems%20that%20the%20companies%20might%20be%20less%20willing%20to%20discuss%20with%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheft%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20shrinkage%20is%20a%20tale%20as%20old%20as%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Melodie%20van%20der%20Baan%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Max%20Retail%2C%20a%20company%20that%20sources%20excess%20inventory%20from%20retailers%20and%20resells%20it.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20always%20be%20a%20thing%2C%20but%20it's%20everything%20else%20that%20you%20have%20to%20manage%20in%20your%20business%20to%20offset%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERetailers%20measure%20theft%20as%20part%20of%20shrink%2C%20but%20that's%20just%20one%20of%20the%20factors%20that%20can%20influence%20their%20bottom%20lines%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETheft%20is%20merely%20one%20cause%20of%20shrink%2C%20which%20added%20up%20to%20%24112.1%20billion%2C%20or%201.6%25%20of%20all%20retail%20sales%2C%20in%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.nrf.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-09%2FNRF_National_Retail_Security_Survey_2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20National%20Retail%20Federation%20released%20in%20September%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExternal%20theft%20accounted%20for%2036%25%20of%20shrink%20in%202022%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20That%20figure%20includes%20the%20impact%20of%20organized%20retail%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20other%20factors%20make%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployee%20theft%20accounted%20for%2029%25%20of%20shrink%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20Another%2027%25%20came%20from%20%26quot%3Bprocess%2C%20control%20failures%20and%20errors%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added%20%E2%80%94%20in%20other%20words%2C%20a%20retailer's%20shortcomings%20in%20tracking%20inventory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20many%20stores%20saw%20shrink%20go%20down%2C%20William%20Blair%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20note%20in%20October.%20Fewer%20people%20were%20shopping%20in%20person%2C%20which%20likely%20led%20to%20fewer%20thefts.%20Many%20turned%20to%20delivery%20services%20such%20as%20Instacart%20to%20get%20food%20and%20other%20essentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20society%20opened%20up%20again%2C%20multiple%20sources%20of%20shrink%20started%20returning%20to%20their%20pre-pandemic%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20also%20had%20to%20order%20enough%20goods%20to%20meet%20fluctuating%20demand%20from%20shoppers.%20After%20a%20run%20on%20toilet%20paper%20and%20other%20goods%20left%20store%20shelves%20bare%20in%202020%2C%20retailers%20including%20Walmart%20put%20in%20larger%20orders%20than%20usual%20with%20suppliers%20to%20ensure%20they%20could%20meet%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22923%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Costco%20coronavirus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e5d077ffee23d753128a002%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22692%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20run%20on%20toilet%20paper%20and%20other%20goods%20left%20store%20shelves%20bare%20in%202020.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FGillian%20Flaccus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20backfired%20in%202022%20as%20shoppers%20returned%20to%20pre-pandemic%20buying%20habits.%20All%20that%20extra%20inventory%20ended%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-employees-describe-inventory-issues-overstocked-stores-2022-7%3Futm_source%3Dreddit.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecluttering%20the%20back%20rooms%20of%20these%20stores%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20retailers%20reduced%20the%20glut%20by%20offering%20discounts%20or%20liquidating%20what%20they%20couldn't%20sell%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20that%20drove%20up%20shrink%2C%20van%20der%20Baan%20said.%20And%20while%20the%20pandemic%20and%20its%20aftershocks%20provided%20a%20striking%20example%2C%20retailers%20often%20struggled%20to%20get%20inventory%20ordering%20right%2C%20even%20in%20%26quot%3Bnormal%26quot%3B%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20short%20on%20supply%2C%20you%20can't%20hit%20your%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20der%20Baan%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you%20overbuy%2C%20and%20things%20don't%20work%20out%20for%20macroeconomic%20reasons%2C%20you're%20also%20not%20hitting%20your%20numbers%2C%20and%20now%20your%20balance%20sheet%20is%20upside%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERetailers%20could%20be%20pointing%20to%20theft%20to%20prompt%20government%20action%20or%20distract%20from%20operational%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20so%20many%20elements%20contribute%20to%20shrink%2C%20then%20why%20are%20some%20retailers%20pointing%20to%20theft%20only%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%2C%20analysts%20at%20William%20Blair%20said%2C%20could%20be%3A%20Laying%20out%20problems%20managing%20inventory%20or%20running%20stores%20could%20draw%20ire%20from%20investors%20and%20others%20on%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Target%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%26quot%3Bcould%20be%20using%20shrink%20to%20mask%20other%20issues%2C%20including%20poor%20inventory%20management%2C%20which%20came%20to%20a%20head%20in%202022%20following%20supply-chain%20disruption%2C%20and%20is%20now%20exiting%20underperforming%20stores%20to%20boost%20overall%20margins%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20note%20this%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20the%20nine%20stores%20that%20Target%20is%20closing%20are%20small-format%20stores%20that%20the%20company%20has%20been%20experimenting%20with%2C%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20exterior%20entrance%20of%20Target%20in%20East%20Harlem%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65202e109f7ca8b2bbdbe5fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Target%20store%20in%20Harlem%2C%20New%20York%2C%20set%20to%20close.%20%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Ortakales%20Dawkins%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShrink%20isn't%20the%20only%20problem%20that%20retailers%20say%20they%20face%20as%20a%20result%20of%20theft.%20Target's%20store-closure%20announcement%20said%20theft%20was%20%26quot%3Bthreatening%20the%20safety%20of%20our%20team%20and%20guests%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20stores%20it%20decided%20to%20close.%20Crime%20data%20from%20those%20locations%2C%20such%20as%20one%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20New%20York%2C%20suggested%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-closing-stores-due-to-crime-stats-tell-another-story-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eclosing%20Targets%20didn't%20suffer%20a%20higher%20amount%20of%20crime%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20than%20others%20that%20are%20remaining%20open%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20could%20be%20calling%20attention%20to%20both%20theft%20and%20related%20violence%20as%20part%20of%20a%20push%20for%20government%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20retailers%20we%20speak%20with%20suggest%20that%20one%20of%20the%20easiest%20actions%20local%20governments%20could%20take%20would%20be%20to%20lower%20the%20dollar%20threshold%20for%20theft%20to%20be%20considered%20a%20felony%20(and%20therefore%20add%20more%20deterrents)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20William%20Blair%20analysts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20that%20kind%20of%20change%20would%20be%20effective%20in%20reducing%20theft%20is%20unclear%2C%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20at%20a%20major%20retail%20store%20such%20as%20Walmart%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40insider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstop-blami