ed%20and%20paid%20fairly%20so%20they%20can%20stay%20in%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Janelle%20Schuurman%2C%20a%2035-year-old%20former%20teacher%20from%20Michigan.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20teacher%20for%2011%20years.%20I%20dreamt%20of%20being%20a%20teacher%20since%20the%20time%20I%20was%20in%20kindergarten.%20I%20actually%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BI'll%20just%20stay%20here%20until%20I'm%20old%20enough%20to%20be%20the%20teacher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20reached%20my%20breaking%20point%20in%202022%2C%20and%20now%20I%20work%20at%20Costco%20because%20I%20got%20so%20burned%20out%20from%20teaching%20elementary%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20at%20what%20was%20once%20my%20dream%20career%2C%20these%20are%20the%20five%20things%20I%20found%20to%20be%20the%20most%20difficult%20about%20being%20a%20teacher%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20The%20job%20never%20ends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20think%20teachers%20have%20a%20cushy%20schedule%20because%20they%20technically%20work%208%20a.m.%20to%203%3A30%20p.m.%20and%20then%20leave%20and%20they%20have%20both%20evenings%20and%20the%20summer%20off%2C%20you're%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20never%20ends%2C%20honestly.%20Every%20day%20you%20have%20to%20spend%20so%20much%20time%20after%20school%20preparing%20for%20the%20next%20day%2C%20and%20there%20are%20always%20extra%20things%20you%20need%20to%20be%20doing.%20I%20would%20typically%20be%20at%20school%20for%2010%20to%2012%20hours%20a%20day%20and%20then%20do%2020%20hours%20of%20work%20per%20week%20outside%20of%20my%20contracted%20hours%20just%20to%20stay%20on%20top%20of%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20reached%20the%20end%20of%20my%20teaching%20career%2C%20I%20started%20to%20feel%20like%20summers%20weren't%20even%20long%20enough%20to%20recharge%20from%20the%20school%20year%2C%20especially%20when%20I%20spent%20so%20much%20of%20the%20summer%20planning%20for%20the%20next%20school%20year.%20It%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20a%20few%20weeks%20off%20instead%20of%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20I%20didn't%20feel%20supported%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20work%20environment%20used%20to%20be%20different%20for%20teachers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nea.org%2Fnea-today%2Fall-news-articles%2Fclass-sizes-growing-issue-among-educators%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClass%20sizes%20used%20to%20be%20more%20reasonable%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20used%20to%20feel%20more%20supported%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20how%20it%20is%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20left%2C%20I%20had%2029%20students%20in%20one%20class%20and%20no%20support%20staff%2C%20like%20teachers'%20aides.%20Ideally%2C%20classes%20shouldn't%20be%20bigger%20than%2020%20to%2022%20students%2C%20especially%20in%20elementary%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20former%20coworkers%20told%20me%20that%2025%20years%20ago%20her%20biggest%20classes%20were%2024%20kids%2C%20and%20she%20would%20have%20a%20paraprofessional%20assistant%20for%20every%20student%20over%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmsutoday.msu.edu%2Fnews%2F2019%2Fmichigan-schools-face-nations-worst-decline-in-state-education-funding%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecreased%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20public%20schools%20plays%20a%20role%20in%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20I%20didn't%20feel%20safe%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20sign%20up%20to%20dive%20in%20front%20of%20bullets%20when%20I%20chose%20education%20as%20a%20career.%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20going%20to%20change%20the%20world%2C%20not%20put%20my%20life%20on%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20the%20day%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftexas-uvalde-robb-elementary-school-shooting-victims-identified-so-far-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUvalde%20shooting%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20just%20felt%20terrified.%20When%20there%20are%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnumber-of-mass-shootingsin-america-this-year-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseemingly%20constant%20mass%20shootings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20hard%20for%20teachers%20to%20feel%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20thought%20I'd%20be%20worried%20about%20my%20safety%20as%20a%20teacher%20%E2%80%94%20but%20by%20the%20end%20of%20my%20teaching%20career%2C%20I%20was%20thinking%20about%20my%20safety%20and%20the%20safety%20of%20my%20students%20constantly.%20Every%20teacher%20in%20my%20school%20had%20a%20walkie-talkie%20in%20case%20they%20had%20to%20call%20for%20help.%20Just%20knowing%20that%20was%20a%20possibility%20was%20horrifying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20I%20resented%20the%20concept%20of%20'focus%20on%20the%20outcome%20versus%20the%20income'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20this%20phrase%20in%20teaching%3A%20Focus%20on%20the%20outcome%20versus%20the%20income.%20The%20whole%20idea%20behind%20this%20is%20just%20the%20guilt-tripping%20of%20teachers%20generally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESociety%20tells%20teachers%3A%20You're%20making%20a%20difference!%20It%20doesn't%20matter%20that%20you%20can%20barely%20make%20ends%20meet!%20This%20is%20your%20passion!%20The%20kids%20need%20you!%20If%20you%20only%20care%20about%20the%20money%2C%20you%20shouldn't%20have%20been%20a%20teacher%20in%20the%20first%20place!%20Do%20it%20for%20the%20kids!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20reality%20is%20teachers%20are%20people%2C%20too.%20We%20should%20be%20able%20to%20make%20a%20living%20doing%20the%20work%20we%20want%20to%20do%2C%20but%20so%20many%20of%20us%20aren't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20lucky%20enough%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20my%20bills%20while%20teaching%2C%20but%20I%20know%20many%20who%20left%20because%20they%20couldn't%20afford%20being%20paid%20such%20a%20low%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Parents'%20and%20politicians'%20backseat%20driving%20was%20exhausting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20seems%20to%20think%20they%20know%20about%20teaching%20just%20because%20they%20were%20once%20a%20student.%20There%20are%20so%20many%20opinions%20from%20people%20outside%20of%20the%20school%2C%20like%20parents%20and%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20think%20we%20should%20teach%20math%20a%20certain%20way%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-critical-race-theory-why-is-gop-so-obsessed-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoid%20certain%20subjects%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Others%20think%20we%20should%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbanned-books-schools-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eban%20some%20books%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20focus%20on%20others.%20It's%20exhausting.%20Teachers%20know%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20and%20they%20need%20to%20be%20allowed%20to%20use%20their%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20want%20to%20solve%20the%20crisis%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-the-teacher-shortage-means-for-four-day-workweek-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20having%20enough%20teachers%20in%20this%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20these%20things%20need%20to%20change.%20Otherwise%2C%20more%20teachers%20might%20follow%20in%20my%20footsteps%20and%20leave%20their%20dream%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20I'm%20happy%20at%20Costco%20because%20I'm%20paid%20fairly%20and%20have%20access%20to%20benefits%20like%20great%20insurance.%20Even%20though%20this%20was%20the%20right%20choice%20for%20me%2C%20I%20never%20thought%20I'd%20leave%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworst-parts-being-teacher-caused-quit-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700215801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6556441622cf74a5739881c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin