women's%20empowerment%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fhindi%2Fsukhee-drops-on-ott-when-and-where-to-watch-this-captivating-slice-of-life-drama%2Farticleshow%2F105284871.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Handcuffs%20for%20Economic%20Offences%2C%20Digital%20Evidence%20'Safeguards'%3A%20Parliamentary%20Panel%20Report%20on%20BNSS%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17131113%2Fimage-1508.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20No%20handcuffing%20for%20economic%20offences%2C%20%E2%80%98robust%20safeguards%E2%80%99%20against%20misuse%20of%20electronic%20evidence%2C%20and%20clarity%20around%20police%20detention%20beyond%2015%20days%20%E2%80%93%20these%20are%20some%20of%20the%20recommendations%20that%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20has%20made%20in%20its%20report%20on%20the%20proposed%20legislation%2C%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20(which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201870)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%20(which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872)%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20parliament%20on%20August%2011%20by%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah.%20They%20were%20then%20referred%20to%20the%2031-member%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20headed%20by%20BJP%20MP%20Brij%20Lal.%20The%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-adopts-reports-on-three-criminal-bills-several-dissent-notes-from-opposition%5C%22%3Eadopted%20%3C%2Fa%3Eits%20report%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Eanalyses%20the%20recommendations%20and%20observations%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20handcuffs%20for%20economic%20offences%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20an%20order%20in%201980%20had%20said%20that%20handcuffs%20are%20against%20human%20dignity%2C%20the%20Bill%20provides%20for%20its%20use%20under%20clause%2043(3)%20for%20certain%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20MPs%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3Edissent%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20also%20flagged%20the%20return%20of%20the%20use%20of%20handcuffs%20and%20said%20that%20the%20Section%20was%20in%20line%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccolonial%20mindset%20of%20punitive%20control%20of%20state%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20report%2C%20however%2C%20the%20parliamentary%20panel%20has%20not%20objected%20to%20its%20use%2C%20except%20in%20the%20case%20of%20economic%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20believes%20that%20the%20use%20of%20handcuffs%2C%20as%20outlined%20in%20Clause%2043(3)%2C%20is%20appropriately%20restricted%20to%20select%20heinous%20crimes%2C%20which%20is%20necessary%20for%20preventing%20the%20escape%20of%20individuals%20accused%20of%20serious%20offences%20and%20ensuring%20the%20safety%20of%20police%20officers%20and%20staff%20during%20arrests%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20committee%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20%E2%80%98economic%20offences%E2%80%99%20should%20not%20be%20included%20in%20this%20category.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98economic%20offences%E2%80%99%20encompasses%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20offences%2C%20ranging%20from%20petty%20to%20serious%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20it%20may%20not%20be%20suitable%20for%20blanket%20application%20of%20handcuffing%20in%20all%20cases%20falling%20under%20this%20category.%20The%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20that%20Clause%2043(3)%20may%20be%20suitably%20amended%20to%20delete%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98economic%20offences%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20clause.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESafeguards%20against%20misuse%20of%20electronic%20evidence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Bill%20advocates%20for%20the%20increasing%20utilisation%20of%20technology%2C%20the%20parliamentary%20panel%20report%2C%20however%2C%20cautions%20against%20electronic%20data%20usage%20without%20safeguards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20says%20that%20trials%2C%20inquiries%2C%20proceedings%20can%20be%20held%20in%20electronic%20mode%2C%20along%20with%20the%20production%20of%20electronic%20communication%20devices%20(such%20as%20mobiles%2C%20computers%2C%20etc.)%2C%20for%20potential%20digital%20evidence%20for%20investigation%2C%20inquiry%20or%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20report%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwhile%20the%20increased%20utilisation%20of%20technology%20offers%20numerous%20advantages%2C%20it%20also%20creates%20opportunities%20for%20manipulation%20and%20misuse.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20the%20collection%20and%20storage%20of%20electronic%20evidence%20raises%20%E2%80%9Cconcerns%20about%20data%20security%20and%20the%20possibility%20of%20unauthorised%20breaches%E2%80%9D%20and%20has%20called%20for%20%E2%80%9Crobust%20safeguards%E2%80%9D%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20that%20the%20adoption%20of%20electronic%20means%20for%20communication%20and%20trials%20should%20proceed%20only%20after%20the%20establishment%20of%20robust%20safeguards%20to%20ensure%20the%20secure%20usage%20and%20authentication%20of%20electronically%20available%20data.%20This%20will%20help%20safeguard%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20justice%20system%20and%20ensure%20that%20justice%20is%20administered%20fairly%20and%20accurately%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20said%20that%20while%20enabling%20online%2Felectronic%20FIR%20registration%20is%20a%20positive%20step%20forward%20in%20the%20proposed%20legislation%2C%20it%20feels%20that%20such%20online%2Felectronic%20registration%20should%20be%20allowed%20only%20through%20modes%20specified%20by%20the%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Bill%20provides%20for%20formal%20adoption%20of%20audio-visual%20and%20electronic%20means%20to%20undertake%20various%20processes%2C%20a%20clause%20may%20be%20inserted%20for%20facilitating%20audio-video%20recording%20of%20evidence%20of%20defence%2C%20after%20ensuring%20proper%20safeguards.%20It%20said%20that%20to%20avoid%20the%20possibility%20of%20tutoring%20or%20intimidation%20of%20witnesses%2C%20such%20recording%20should%20only%20be%20allowed%20at%20select%20government%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeed%20clarity%20on%20the%20extended%20period%20of%20police%20custody%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20has%20also%20sought%20greater%20clarity%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20increased%20period%20of%20police%20custody%2C%20an%20issue%20that%20had%20been%20raised%20by%20the%20opposition%20MPs%20in%20their%20dissent%20notes.%20The%20MPs%20had%20referred%20to%20Clause%20187%20that%20allows%20the%20magistrate%20to%20increase%20the%20period%20of%20police%20custody%20beyond%2015%20days%20under%20certain%20circumstances%2C%20and%20said%20that%20increasing%20the%20period%20of%20police%20custody%20without%20proper%20safeguards%20could%20lead%20to%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20report%20noted%20that%20Clause%20187(2)%20stipulates%20a%20total%20of%2015%20days%20for%20police%20custody%2C%20to%20be%20utilised%20in%20whole%20or%20in%20parts%20at%20any%20time%20during%20the%20initial%2040%20days%20or%2060%20days%20out%20of%20the%20detention%20period%20of%2060%20days%20or%2090%20days%2C%20as%20applicable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20there%20is%20a%20concern%20that%20this%20clause%20could%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20misuse%20by%20authorities%2C%20as%20it%20does%20not%20explicitly%20clarify%20that%20the%20custody%20was%20not%20taken%20in%20the%20first%2015%20days%20either%20due%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20accused%20or%20due%20to%20extraneous%20circumstances%20beyond%20the%20control%20of%20the%20investigating%20officer.%20The%20committee%20recommends%20that%20a%20suitable%20amendment%20may%20be%20brought%20to%20provide%20greater%20clarity%20in%20the%20interpretation%20of%20this%20clause%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20must%20provide%20reasons%20for%20commuting%20sentences%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20power%20of%20the%20government%20to%20commute%20a%20sentence%20under%20Clause%20475%20of%20the%20new%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20in%20its%20report%20has%2C%20however%2C%20only%20recommended%20amending%20Clause%20475(b)%20to%20specify%20both%20a%20minimum%20and%20maximum%20sentence%20that%20can%20be%20imposed%20on%20convicts%20while%20commuting%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20to%20a%20shorter%20term.%20It%20has%20also%20directed%20that%20the%20government%20must%20provide%20reasons%20for%20commuting%20a%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20ensure%20that%20the%20power%20given%20to%20the%20appropriate%20government%20to%20commute%20a%20sentence%20is%20judiciously%20used%20and%20the%20commutation%20is%20justified%2C%20the%20committee%20recommends%20that%20appropriate%20reasons%20may%20be%20cited%20before%20commutation%20of%20a%20sentence%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700207235000%2C%22visual%22%3A