r%20printed%20in%20the%20style%20of%20the%20Times%C2%A0and%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20New%20York%20War%20Crimes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20of%20the%20night%20was%20to%20to%20shame%20the%20organization%20behind%20the%20gala%2C%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%2C%20for%20selecting%20Meredith%20Kopit%20Levien%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20president%20of%20the%20paper's%20parent%20company%2C%20as%20chair%20of%20its%20annual%20Press%20Freedom%20Awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20Business%20Insider%20ahead%20of%20the%20protest%2C%20journalist%20and%20organizer%20Harron%20Walker%20said%20the%20group%20singled%20out%20the%20Times%20in%20part%20because%20of%20its%20respected%20status%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bpaper%20of%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20organizers%20were%20also%20incensed%20by%20a%20November%203%20op-ed%20by%20the%20paper's%20editorial%20board%20that%20argued%20against%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20citing%20Israeli%20concerns%20that%20such%20a%20move%20would%20only%20allow%20Hamas%20to%20re-arm%20and%20reinforce%20its%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20them%20to%20go%20about%20with%20business%20as%20usual%20and%20even%20celebrating%20themselves%20as%20protectors%20of%20journalists%2C%26quot%3B%20Walker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20of%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20and%20the%20Times%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20at%20the%20center%20of%20Thursday's%20protest%2C%20Writers%20Against%20the%20War%20on%20Gaza%2C%20or%20WAWOG%2C%20coalesced%20around%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.writersagainstthewarongaza.com%5C%22%3Eopen%20letter%20issued%20on%20October%2026%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20letter%20%E2%80%94%20which%20labels%20Israel%20an%20apartheid%20state%20and%20accuses%20it%20of%20committing%20genocide%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20the%20coalition%20declares%20solidarity%