kidnappers-13009982%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fluis-diazs-father-weeps-as-his-son-scores-twice-for-colombia-against-brazil-days-after-release-by-kidnappers-13009982%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20People%20Killed%20By%20Aerial%20Bombing%20Don't%20Matter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20November%2017%2C%2041%20days%20into%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20continuous%20bombardment%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F16%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fuk-labour-party-ceasefire-vote-gaza.html%5C%22%3EUK%20Parliament%20voted%20against%20a%20motion%20calling%20for%20an%20ceasefire%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bombing%20continues%2C%20and%20one%20question%20stands%20out%3A%20Why%201%2C200%20people%20killed%20by%20guerillas%20matter%20more%20to%20Western%20governments%20than%2012%2C000%20%E2%80%93%20and%20counting%20%E2%80%93%20killed%20by%20bombs%20from%20the%20sky.%20Why%20one%20is%20a%20barbaric%20crime%2C%20and%20the%20other%20a%20civilised%20military%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20correct%20answers%20to%20that.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20the%20history%20of%20bombing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20single%20line%3A%20From%20its%20beginnings%2C%20over%20a%20hundred%20years%20ago%2C%20aerial%20bombing%20was%20a%20technology%20meant%20for%20colonial%20powers%20to%20use%20exclusively%20against%20colonised%2C%20usually%20indigenous%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20hundred%20years%2C%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20monopoly%20over%20that%20most%20lethal%20violence%20has%20conditioned%20how%20we%20see%20the%20victims%20of%20bombs%20%E2%80%93%20if%20we%20see%20them%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20aeroplanes%20to%20drop%20lethal%20explosives%20is%20nearly%20as%20old%20as%20powered%20flight%20itself.%20The%20technology%20was%20primitive%20when%20the%20First%20World%20War%20broke%20out%20in%20Europe%2C%20and%20never%20became%20a%20decisive%20military%20factor%20in%20the%20war.%20Afterwards%2C%20though%2C%20its%20potential%20was%20obvious%3A%20the%20danger%20and%20the%20power%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESven%20Lindqvist%2C%20in%20his%20inventive%20book-essay%20%3Cem%3EA%20History%20of%20Bombing%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20describes%20what%20followed%20in%20the%20inter-war%20years.%20European%20governments%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Prepared%20treaties%20to%20never%20bomb%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Decided%20to%20use%20colonial%20targets%20as%20sites%20to%20test%2C%20refine%20and%20advance%20the%20technology%20of%20bombing%20from%20the%20air%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Began%20creating%20air%20forces%20primarily%20for%20%E2%80%98aerial%20policing%E2%80%99%3A%20which%20often%20meant%20bombing%20tribal%20villages%20prone%20to%20political%20unrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBritain%2C%20to%20take%20one%20example%2C%20was%20a%20victorious%20nation%20in%201919%2C%20but%20cash-strapped%20and%20shaken%2C%20with%20its%20hold%20on%20empire%20slipping.%20One%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20named%20Winston%20Churchill%2C%20came%20to%20hold%20three%20portfolios%20at%20the%20same%20time%3A%20for%20The%20Colonies%2C%20Air%20and%20War.%20With%20Hugh%20Trenchard%2C%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20first%20chief%20of%20air%20staff%2C%20Churchill%20conceived%20a%20military%20doctrine%20%E2%80%93%20also%20a%20budgetary%20argument%20%E2%80%93%20for%20%E2%80%9Caerial%20policing%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20far%20reaches%20of%20the%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20power%2C%20they%20realised%2C%20could%20relieve%20the%20empire%20of%20costly%20army%20garrisons.%20As%20young%20men%20and%20soldiers%2C%20both%20Churchill%20and%20Trenchard%20had%20served%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpolicing%E2%80%9D%20of%20colonial%20frontiers%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20in%20Waziristan%20and%20West%20Africa%20respectively.%20Churchill%E2%80%99s%20first%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EWith%20the%20Malakand%20Field%20Force%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20described%20the%20arduous%20work%20of%20exacting%20collective%20punishment%20on%20Pashtuns.%20Regiments%20advanced%2C%20dynamiting%20buildings%2C%20felling%20orchards%20and%20filling%20up%20wells%20with%20rocks%20and%20gravel%20(tactics%20still%20favoured%20by%20Israeli%20settlers%20and%20the%20IDF%20against%20Palestinian%20villages%20in%20the%20West%20Bank).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20Churchill%20wrote%2C%20they%20%E2%80%9Cdestroyed%20all%20the%20villages%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20valley%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20whole%20valley%20was%20filled%20with%20the%20smoke%2C%20which%20curled%20upwards%20in%20dense%20and%20numerous%20columns%2C%20and%20hung%20like%20a%20cloud%20over%20the%20scene%20of%20destruction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20comparative%20efficiency%20of%20achieving%20this%20from%20the%20air%2C%20with%20bombing%20raids%2C%20was%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F05%2Fguernica3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-139765%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22556%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPablo%20Picasso%E2%80%99s%20Guernica.%20Photo%3A%20pablopicasso.org%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201920%2C%20the%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20carried%20out%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20systematic%20bombing%20campaign%20against%20Somalis.%20Thereafter%2C%20the%20first%20societies%20in%20to%20experience%20bombing%20were%20in%20Iraq%2C%20North%20and%20East%20Africa%2C%20and%20the%20North-West%20Frontier%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArthur%20Harris%2C%20later%20a%20legend%20of%20British%20bomber%20command%2C%20said%20this%20early%20in%20his%20career%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Arab%20and%20Kurd%20now%20know%20what%20real%20bombing%20means%2C%20in%20casualties%20and%20damage.%20They%20know%20that%20within%2045%20minutes%2C%20a%20full-sized%20village%20can%20be%20practically%20wiped%20out%2C%20and%20a%20third%20of%20its%20inhabitants%20killed%20or%20injured.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20an%20eerie%20continuity%20between%20those%20places%20and%20the%20ones%20still%20being%20bombed%20on%20Western%20order%20a%20century%20later.%20While%20writing%20my%20own%20book%20%3Cem%3EFarthest%20Field%3A%20An%20Indian%20Story%20of%20the%20Second%20World%20War%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%202013%2C%20I%20researched%20the%20bombing%20raids%20on%20two%20Pashtun%20villages%2C%20Ahmed%20Khel%20and%20Datta%20Khel%2C%20in%201941.%20Looking%20up%20their%20names%20online%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20those%20exact%20villages%20were%20still%20being%20punished%20by%20Predator%20drones%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Western%20ethics%20of%20aerial%20bombing%2C%20wrote%20Sven%20Lindqvist%2C%20made%20this%20very%20clear%3A%20%E2%80%98The%20laws%20of%20war%20protect%20enemies%20of%20the%20same%20race%2C%20class%2C%20and%20culture.%20The%20laws%20of%20war%20leave%20the%20foreign%20and%20the%20alien%20without%20protection.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201940s%2C%20once%20World%20War%20II%20broke%20out%20in%20Europe%2C%20these%20rules%20could%20not%20hold.%20And%20there%20was%20hell%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bombing%20of%20Guernica%20in%201937%2C%20by%20German%20and%20Italian%20air%20forces%2C%20was%20a%20herald%20that%20civilian%20bombardment%20would%20be%20turned%20against%20Europeans%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20always%20happens%2C%20and%20is%20the%20central%20insight%20of%20Lindqvist%E2%80%99s%20writings%3A%20technologies%20of%20control%20meant%20for%20colonial%20peripheries%20come%20home%20to%20roost%20in%20the%20metropole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20years%20of%20World%20War%20II%20were%20an%20exception.%20In%20the%20post-war%20world%2C%20bombing%20resumed%20on%20the%20same%20racial%2C%20colonial%20lines%20and%20geographies%2C%20right%20through%20the%20US%20wars%20on%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20in%20this%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20two%20countries%20push%20this%20colonial%20perversity%20into%20newer%20and%20deadlier%20expressions%3A%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Israel.%20Since%20October%2C%20reports%20say%20Israel%20has%20dropped%20more%20than%2025%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20explosives%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20That%20is%20equivalent%20to%20two%20nuclear%20bombs.%20The%20Gaza%20Strip%20has%20an%20area%20about%20one%20quarter%20the%20size%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20deflection%20and%20defence%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20%E2%80%93%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20trying%20to%20hit%20civilians%2C%20Hamas%20is%20at%20fault%20for%20placing%20its%20fighters%20among%20civilians%20%E2%80%93%20is%20old%20news%2C%20straight%20from%20a%20hundred-year-old%20textbook%20for%20colonial%20collective%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20Israeli%20commanders%20have%20been%20saying%20it%20out%20loud%2C%20from%20day%20one%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20emphasis%20is%20on%20damage%2C%20not%20on%20accuracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20hundred%20years%2C%20our%20moral%20imagination%20of%20war%20has%20been%20shaped%20by%20colonizing%20states%20which%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20bomb%20from%20the%20air%2C%20and%20want%20to%20use%20it%3A%20Against%20tribes%20on%20their%20own%20native%20land.%20Against%20people%20with%20barely%20any%20defences.%20Against%20civilians.%20The%20perpetrators%20of%20this%20mass%20killing%20are%20always%20coded%20as%20civilized.%20The%20victims%20are%20always%20at%20best%20invisible%2C%20at%20worst%20sub-human.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20also%20been%20conditioned%20is%20our%20visual%20imagination.%20For%20weeks%2C%20most%20images%20from%20Gaza%20only%20showed%20explosions%20from%20a%20distance%2C%20collapsing%20buildings%2C%20smoking%20ruins.%20When%20we%20do%20see%20the%20victims%20%E2%80%93%20children%20buried%20alive%20under%20masonry%2C%20or%20people%20carrying%20the%20destroyed%20bodies%20of%20their%20friends%2C%20looking%20for%20help%20%E2%80%93%20we%E2%80%99re%20trained%20to%20not%20see%20them%20as%20fully%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2026%2C%20weeks%20into%20the%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza%2C%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20voted%20overwhelmingly%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%2C%20durable%20and%20sustained%20humanitarian%20truce%E2%80%9D.%20One%20hundred%20and%20twenty%20countries%20votes%20in%20favour%20and%2014%20voted%20against.%20India%20was%20among%20the%2045%20that%20abstained.%20It%20was%20a%20measure%20of%20the%20real%20international%20demand%20for%20Israel%20to%20stop%20bombing.%20But%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20double%20standards%20have%20been%20unmoving%2C%20with%20hugely%20damaging%20effects%20on%20what%20survives%20of%20international%20law%20and%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20you%20read%20this%2C%20more%20people%20in%20Gaza%20are%20being%20buried%20alive%20by%20bombs%2C%20and%20Western%20leaders%20will%20not%20utter%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98ceasefire%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20for%20that%3A%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20a%20few%20years%20in%20the%201940s%2C%20the%20people%20being%20bombed%20from%20the%20air%20were%20rarely%20European.%20And%20except%20for%20one%20day%20in%202001%2C%20they%20were%20never%20American.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20people%20dropping%20the%20bombs%20usually%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERaghu%20Karnad%20is%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Dorothy%20and%20Lewis%20B.%20Cullman%20Center%20for%20Scholars%20%26amp%3B%20Writers%2C%20New%20York%20Public%20Library%2C%202022-23.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700192689000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38