ny%20planets%20in%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExoplanet%20scientists%20have%20enough%20data%20now%20to%20say%20that%20this%20gap%20is%20not%20a%20fluke.%20There's%20something%20going%20on%20that%20impedes%20planets%20from%20reaching%20and%2For%20staying%20at%20this%20size%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-nasa-scientist-dinosaurs-milky-way-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJessie%20Christiansen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20research%20scientist%20at%20Caltech%20and%20science%20lead%20for%20the%20NASA%20Exoplanet%20Archive%2C%20said%20in%20a%20Wednesday%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20think%20this%20is%20because%20some%20sub-Neptunes%20shrink%20%E2%80%94%20losing%20their%20atmospheres%20and%20speeding%20through%20the%20size%20gap%20until%20they%20are%20as%20small%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-super-earth-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuper-Earth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225181%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20exoplanet%20HAT-P-7b%2C%20which%20is%201000%20light-years%20away%20from%20Earth.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65554a3c4ca513d8242a48b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223434%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20exoplanet%20HAT-P-7b%2C%20which%20is%201%2C000%20light-years%20away%20from%20Earth.%3Cp%3EMark%20Garlick%20%2F%20Science%20Photo%20Library%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChristiansen's%20latest%20research%20suggests%20those%20worlds%20shrink%20because%20radiation%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearth-core-encased-by-ancient-ocean-mountains-taller-everest-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20planets'%20cores%3C%2Fa%3E%20pushes%20their%20atmospheres%20away%2C%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.3847%2F1538-3881%2Facf9f9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20in%20The%20Astronomical%20Journal%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20might%20solve%20the%20mystery%20of%20the%20missing%20exoplanets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20planets%20themselves%20may%20be%20pushing%20their%20atmospheres%20away%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShrinking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-exoplanets-discovered-astronomers-find-water-alien-worlds-life-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexoplanets%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20lack%20the%20mass%20(and%20therefore%20the%20gravity)%20to%20hold%20their%20atmospheres%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exact%20mechanism%20for%20the%20atmosphere%20loss%2C%20however%2C%20remains%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20study%20supports%20one%20hypothesis%20scientists%20call%20%26quot%3Bcore-powered%20mass%20loss%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECore-powered%20mass%20loss%20is%20not%20a%20trendy%20new%20workout%20plan.%20It's%20when%20a%20planet's%20core%20emits%20radiation%20that%20pushes%20its%20atmosphere%20from%20underneath%2C%20leading%20to%20it%20separating%20from%20the%20planet%20over%20time%2C%20per%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20hypothesis%2C%20called%20photoevaporation%2C%20says%20that%20a%20planet's%20atmosphere%20is%20dissipated%20by%20the%20radiation%20of%20its%20host%20star.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20photoevaporation%20is%20thought%20to%20occur%20by%20the%20time%20a%20planet%20is%20100%20million%20years%20old%20%E2%80%94%20and%20core-powered%20mass%20loss%20could%20happen%20closer%20to%20the%20planet's%20one%20billionth%20birthday%2C%20per%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20test%20the%20two%20hypotheses%2C%20Christiansen's%20team%20looked%20at%20data%20from%20NASA's%20retired%20Kepler%20Space%20Telescope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20examined%20star%20clusters%20that%20were%20over%20100%20million%20years%20old.%20Because%20planets%20are%20thought%20to%20be%20roughly%20the%20same%20age%20as%20their%20host%20stars%2C%20the%20planets%20in%20these%20clusters%20would%20be%20old%20enough%20to%20have%20experienced%20photoevaporation%2C%20but%20not%20old%20enough%20for%20core-powered%20mass%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20found%20that%20most%20of%20the%20planets%20there%20retained%20their%20atmosphere%2C%20making%20the%20core-powered%20mass%20loss%20a%20more%20likely%20cause%20of%20eventual%20atmosphere%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20recent%20work%20suggests%20an%20ongoing%20mass-loss%20sequence%20where%20both%20processes%20operate%2C%26quot%3B%20Christiansen%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20the%20platform%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20sharing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fui.adsabs.harvard.edu%2Fabs%2F2023arXiv230800020O%2Fabstract%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elink%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20Harvard%20assessment%20posted%20online%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20mystery%20isn't%20solved%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Christiansen's%20statement%20in%20the%20release%2C%20her%20work%20isn't%20over%20yet%20either%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20because%20our%20understanding%20of%20exoplanets%20will%20develop%20with%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-planets-shrinking-atmosphere-core-radiation-exoplanet-scientists-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700186121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6556a0da4ca513d8242b20dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-planets-shrinking-atmosphere-core-radiation-exoplanet-scientists-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mystery%20of%20a%20missing%20class%20of%20planets%20has%20had%20NASA%20astronomers%20scratching%20their%20heads.%20New%20evidence%20suggests%20radiation%20could%20be%20behind%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22scahill%40businessinsider.com%20